   api_appendClientRow_, api_updateClientRow_, handleOnboardClient_.
   v38.36.0: TWO fixes for onboarding:
   (1) api_appendClientRow_ now writes to ALL columns with the same header name (freshHMapAll multi-index map). Root cause: Justin's CB Clients sheet has DUPLICATE "Web App URL" columns. Previous code wrote to the LAST occurrence (per JS object semantics), but handleGetClients_ used sheetToObjects_ which might read the other duplicate, causing the React Edit modal to show an empty Web App URL even though the deploy succeeded. Now writes hit all duplicates. Also surfaces the duplicate headers as a warning so the user knows to clean them up.
   (2) handleFinishClientSetup_ now LIST's existing deployments via the Apps Script API first, and REUSES any existing Web App deployment instead of creating a new one. Fixes two problems: (a) Arkitektura Forty already has a working deployment but the URL never landed in CB Clients — reuse reads the URL from the existing deployment and writes it to all duplicate columns. (b) Clicking Finish Setup multiple times no longer creates orphan deployments for the same script.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.35.0 — 2026-04-10 — Script ID discovery fix (folder search + Settings tab _SCRIPT_ID fallback)
   v38.35.0: Root cause of "Could not find the bound Apps Script project" — DriveApp.searchFiles with "'sheetId' in parents" does NOT reliably find container-bound scripts because bound scripts don't show up as children of their spreadsheet in Drive's parent-child queries. New multi-strategy discovery:
   (1) handleOnboardClient_: primary search is now "scripts in the client FOLDER" (where makeCopy() places the new bound script), matching by name. Falls back to legacy sheet-parent search if folder search returns nothing.
   (2) handleFinishClientSetup_: 4-strategy lookup: (a) CB Clients Script ID column, (b) client sheet's Settings tab _SCRIPT_ID row (written automatically whenever any Stride Admin menu action runs — verifyTriggers writes ScriptApp.getScriptId() there), (c) Drive search within client folder by name, (d) legacy sheet-parent search. Strategy (b) is the MOST RELIABLE because the bound script writes its own ID after any user action on the sheet.
   Error message updated to tell the user to click any Stride Admin menu item inside the client sheet to register the script ID.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.34.0 — 2026-04-10 — Script ID retry + warning text updates
   v38.34.0: (1) handleOnboardClient_ now retries script ID discovery via Drive search with backoff delays (0, 1s, 3s, 5s, 7s — total max wait ~16s). Drive indexing lag after makeCopy() typically resolves within 2-8 seconds, so most onboardings will now auto-deploy the Web App without needing Finish Setup. (2) All outdated CLI warning messages ("run npm run sync && npm run deploy-clients", "run npm run install-triggers") replaced with instructions to click the in-app "Finish Setup" button. Justin's team can't run npm commands, so pointing them at the CLI was a dead end.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.33.0 — 2026-04-10 — Onboarding Web App URL write fix
   v38.33.0: Fixed two bugs that caused "Web App URL" and "Deployment ID" columns to stay empty even after successful onboarding:
   (1) api_appendClientRow_ now returns { targetRow, freshHMap, writtenCount, ... } so callers know exactly which row was written and have the fresh header map.
   (2) handleOnboardClient_ Web App URL write now uses clientRowInfo.targetRow (exact row from the append) and clientRowInfo.freshHMap (fresh lookup). Previously used api_getLastDataRow_() which had a race-condition risk, and the stale clientsHMap snapshot from before the append which could miss columns. Writes are also logged and any missing columns surface as warnings in the response.
   Audit finding: Import Inventory URL feature from the legacy GAS flow is NOT ported to the React backend — the payload accepts importInventoryUrl but it's currently ignored. Non-critical (only used for legacy sheet migration). Will port if needed.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.32.0 — 2026-04-10 — Fix freeStorageDays 0-coercion bug
   v38.32.0: handleOnboardClient_ was using `Number(payload.freeStorageDays) || 30` which treats 0 as falsy and silently replaces it with 30. Same for discountStoragePct/discountServicesPct (replaced explicit 0 with... still 0, so no visible bug, but inconsistent). Now uses explicit null/empty-string check. Matches the Master Inventory Template which defaults Free Storage Days to 0.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.31.0 — 2026-04-10 — finishClientSetup recovery + appendClientRow rewrite
   v38.31.0: (1) New handleFinishClientSetup_ endpoint for recovering partially-onboarded clients where the Web App was never deployed (Drive indexing lag, transient failures). Takes clientSheetId, re-runs script ID discovery + Web App deploy + trigger install. Idempotent. Powers the in-app "Finish Setup" button. Replaces the "npm run sync && npm run deploy-clients" CLI fallback. (2) api_appendClientRow_ rewritten for robustness: re-reads header row fresh from sheet (no stale snapshot), writes each cell individually (one bad cell no longer kills others), logs missing columns, includes Auto Charge field (was missing). Fixes "only Client Name + Email saved, everything else blank" bug that occurred when the header snapshot was out of sync with the actual sheet.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.30.0 — 2026-04-10 — Onboarding row-write grid auto-expansion
   v38.30.0: api_appendClientRow_ now calls insertRowsAfter() before setValues() when the target row exceeds the sheet's current maxRows. Fixes "The coordinates of the range are outside the dimensions of the sheet" when CB Clients tab has been trimmed to just filled rows. Also guards against insufficient columns (insertColumnsAfter). Client row write is now safe regardless of sheet size.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.29.0 — 2026-04-10 — Onboarding row-write data validation bypass
   v38.29.0: api_appendClientRow_ now calls range.clearDataValidations() before setValues(), so stale dropdown rules on the CB Clients "Payment Terms" column (e.g. ALL-CAPS values) can't block the row write. Previously, the setValues() throw was caught as a silent warning and the client row was never appended, leaving a "ghost" client (spreadsheet exists but not in the Clients tab). The validation bypass only affects the row being written, not the header row.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.28.0 — 2026-04-10 — Bulk Sync per-client column fix
   v38.28.0: handleBulkSyncToSupabase_ and handleReconcileSupabase_ per-client branches were looking up rows by "Spreadsheet ID" (typo), but the CB Clients tab column is "Client Spreadsheet ID" (used by every other handler in the file). Pre-existing bug since v36.0.0; only surfaced when the React per-client loop started calling these paths. Fixed both to use the correct column name.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.27.0 — 2026-04-10 — handleRemoteAction_ token fix
   v38.27.0: handleRemoteAction_ now sends REMOTE_EXEC_TOKEN ("stride-remote-exec-9f3a2") instead of API_TOKEN. Clients' RemoteAdmin.gs doPost checks against their hardcoded REMOTE_EXEC_TOKEN_ constant, not the API_TOKEN property. Previously all clients (except Master Inventory Template for historical reasons) returned "unauthorized" on updateHeaders / installTriggers. Configurable via CLIENT_REMOTE_EXEC_TOKEN Script Property if token ever rotates.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.26.0 — 2026-04-10 — handleRemoteAction_ error propagation
   v38.26.0: handleRemoteAction_ now populates BOTH `message` and `error` fields on failed results so React's `r.error` display works. Previously on HTTP 200 + body.ok=false, the failure reason landed in `message` but React only read `error`, producing empty error lines. Also falls back to raw truncated body if body.message is empty (surfaces HTML error pages etc). Added sheetId to each result for proper React key usage.
   StrideAPI.gs — v38.25.0 — 2026-04-10 — Transfer Date cutover for storage billing
   v38.25.0: handleTransferItems_ accepts transferDate (YYYY-MM-DD, defaults to today, past allowed, future rejected). New "Transfer Date" column auto-added to source + destination Inventory tabs (api_ensureColumn_ helper). Storage billing splits at the cutover: source bills receive→(transferDate-1), destination bills transferDate→endDate with FRESH free-days credit. Released items still skipped if no Release Date. React TransferItemsModal exposes Transfer Date input (defaults today, max today). No backfill needed (no live transferred items yet).
   v38.24.0: handleGenerateStorageCharges_ + handlePreviewStorageCharges_ now include Released and On Hold items in storage billing for the days they were physically in stock. Released items require a Release Date (skipped with warning otherwise). Existing release-date math (-1 day convention) handled the calculation correctly — only the over-restrictive status filter needed to change. Transferred items still excluded (destination client inherits via transfer flow).
